Set 1

Not Fade Away-> Touch Of Gray, Tons Of Steel, CC Rider, Dupree's Diamond Blues, Cassidy-> Brown Eyed Women, Let It Grow

reviews.review_text: NEW YEARS ENERGY..... Decent "Off Air" recording. The boys come out and appear to feed off the crowd and launch into NFA instead of TOG! High energy show!
Chatty Bobby Bobby is a little chatty in this one - maybe because it is a radio broadcast.  Great sound matrix.  Nice CC Rider, LIG and double encore.

New Year's Eve UnderEstimated I will grant you - that there are other Nye shows that are longer than this and (I guess for some people) stronger b/c of that.

Another complaint I remember at the time was that the boys did not do a 3rd set.

But what I notice when I listen to this (again after 26 years) was the same thing I noticed when taping it back then: the electricity between the crowd and the boys.

Set one is solid with a NFA opener (even when commentator says..."sounds like nfa to me."). The segue into touch was awesome b/c while the boys had been playing touch for some time, it was not "burned out". The rest of the set is above average. Nothing really out of the ordinairy - but solid play, just as they had done at most of their shows in '85.

The midnight hour>Sugaree really was awesome. It is easy in retrospect to look back and wonder "why not break out St. Stephen or Dark Star? But the thing is the boys had revived many tunes in '85 including crazy fingers, cryptical big boy pete, big boss man, kansas city, baby what you want me to do. I know that is not an exhaustive list. 
The playing is stellar after that women>ship>playin>terrapintruckin>blackpeter>throwinstones>nfa>nfa reprise> lovelight//brokedown.
Very solid show and one that I think deserves more credit than some are giving it. 

God Bless and Enjoy!
